An image and a question will be displayed. The task is to decide whether the question is [VALID] or [INVALID].

Example Image 1

[VALID] Q:"Are there any men to the left of the seagull?" Ans: Yes

[VALID] Q:"Are there any young men to the left of the seagull?" Ans: No

[VALIDS] Q:"Are there any old men to the left of the seagull?" Ans: Yes

[INVALID] Q:"Are there any men to the left of the red seagull?" This is invalid because there is no red seagull.

[INVALID] Q:"What type of fast food is to the left of the man who wears a coat?" This is invalid because there is no fast food to the left of the man who wears a coat.

[VALID] Q:"What are the animals in front of the fence?" Ans: Giraffe

[INVALID] Q:"What are the animals in front of the bottle?" This is invalid because there is no bottle.

[INVALID] Q:"What are the green animals in front of the brown fence?" This is invalid because there is no green animals or brown fence.

Example Image 3

[INVALID] Q:"What is in the green pocket?" This is invalid because there is no green pocket.

[VALID] Q:"Is the person that is looking up wearing a cap?" Ans: Yes

[VALID] Q:"Is the person that is looking up wearing a green cap?" Ans: No

[INVALID] Q:"Is the elderly person that is looking up wearing a cap?" This is invalid because there is no elderly person.

Instruction: Is this a valid question? Select [VALID] or [INVALID]. An invalid question are questions that you are unable to answer based on images. For example, if the question is "What is the color of the dog next to the cat", but there is no cat in the image, this is an invalid question. However, if the question is "Is there a cat in the image?", one can answer "No", which makes this a VALID question. Note that if you can answer the question, it is a VALID question, regardless of the answer (the answer can not be nobody, nothing, nowhere etc.). See more VALID/INVALID examples below and click instruction on top left for more examples.
